M||tx|---
M||titl|Calculate Derived State During Rendering
M||impa|md
M||impa|avoids redundant renders and state drift
M||tags|rerender, derived-state, useEffect, state
M||tx|---
M|Calc|tx|If a value can be computed from current props/state, do not store it in state or up it in an effect. Derive it during render to avoid extra renders and state drift. Do not set state in effects solely in rp to prop changes; prefer derived values or keyed resets instead.
M|Calc|**In|**
M|Calc|tx|```tsx
M|Calc|tx|fn Form() {
M|Calc|tx|const [firstName, setFirstName] = useState('First')
M|Calc|tx|const [lastName, setLastName] = useState('Last')
M|Calc|tx|const [fullName, setFullName] = useState('')
M|Calc|tx|useEffect(() => {
M|Calc|tx|setFullName(firstName + ' ' + lastName)
M|Calc|tx|}, [firstName, lastName])
M|Calc|tx|return <p>{fullName}</p>
M|Calc|tx|}
M|Calc|tx|```
M|Calc|**Co|**
M|Calc|tx|```tsx
M|Calc|tx|fn Form() {
M|Calc|tx|const [firstName, setFirstName] = useState('First')
M|Calc|tx|const [lastName, setLastName] = useState('Last')
M|Calc|tx|const fullName = firstName + ' ' + lastName
M|Calc|tx|return <p>{fullName}</p>
M|Calc|tx|}
M|Calc|tx|```
M|Calc|Refe|[You Might Not Need an Effect](https://rc.dv/learn/you-might-not-need-an-effect)